snippet.textDisplay: I hope to god that fans understand that Ole isn't the problem. Ole holds this badge to higher standard and that's why he would rather start fro scratch with a whole crop of young talent rather than work with what he had at the moment. It's the culture that surrounds the club for the past 7 years and right now we need someone that can restore the the culture we used to have before ever considering winning titles. There is no short fix, the damage has already been done. But people need to stay behind Ole because he's not the problem.

snippet.textDisplay:
The reason recent Liverpool signings have become successful is that they signed with a clear vision and plan. Klopp have a team, a playing style and defined roles/player profiles for the required playing style in his mind and brought these players according to this thought process. He was a proven manager at the league and Europe level and did it before with Dortmund playing very good football with players like Piczcek, Bender, Blaczykowski etc. punching well above their weight. He's doing the same with Henderson, Milner, Wijnaldum etc. That's called good coaching. None of Liverpool players were world beaters before Klopp (actually City released Milner, Henderson was as mediocre as they come, Wijnaldum was a midtable midfielder etc.) and now they are part of a working machine. Fergie did the same for years. He won time and time again with the likes of Fletcher, Brown, O'shea etc.


The impact and importance of a manager is clear to see. We need a top coach more than we need players. We can blame Glazers & the clown named Woodward all we want but at the end of the day they're not the ones who prepares the team and they have spent money. Last summer we were the biggest spenders again. Woodward or Glazers didn't decide to spend most of his budget on a CB who is slower than a turtle and with clear weaknesses in the summer. They didn't decide to ignore the midfield and right wing.


Why this guy says nothing about our clueless manager and refuses to blame him? Because Ole's an ex-United player? We're as bad as Moyes season now but only difference is the mediocrity and the results like that have become acceptable. That's the biggest achievement of Ole and Woodward & Glazers. Lowering the expectations, making everyone believe it's OK to be in this mess. We're lucky that all of City, Chelsea, Spurs, Arsenal, Everton etc. are wank this season and we're not that far behind in the table in terms of position. But that's also misleading as we also could finish as low as 9th or 10th still because the difference in points is just 7 with 14th place now. How's that acceptable for Manchester United? It wasn't under Moyes, Van Gaal or Mourinho but it is now under Ole. Hypocrite & Deluded. We're not getting back from this mess with this kind of delusion and sentimentality. Get a competent manager who is tactically astute and get some quality players.

snippet.textDisplay:
Agreed. It's hard to replace a legend of a manager, but more so the structure hasn't changed with the times. Even Sir Alex had misses in the market or trusting an academy player wrong, but he not only had a clearplan, he had backroom staff who helped either scouting it signing quickly and effortlessly. There hasn't been that since Moyes.
I compare it to my face baseball team, my Yankees. They tried simply out spending everyone to no end with sh/t results. It was t until upper management said we need to replan and stick to it that they began winning again. Sometimes that meant not buying the $150 mil player. Sometimes it meant paying extra for the final piece. United need that same level of planning. Buying off names alone got us here. Barely holding 5th because other powers are just as dysfunctional as us.

snippet.textDisplay: Well I think there was no planned structure by all those involved in this rebuild after Sir Alex has left. Everyone has done their bit individually rather than a unit to build the club again. Everyone wants to point fingers at somewhere or someone to take the blame. There is no culture in the recruitment and negotiation, there is no development or strategic idea on the football to be played and game management. Every single thing done by someone from the club is completely reactive based decisions. Nothing is proactive, there is no approach of a superior quality or talent for the roles available. It's a bit of mix and match at freewill while compensating on average as a means to recuperate the money spent. The only thing pleasing my heart is the quality of young boys coming through the academy, god bless Nicky Butt for overseeing this project. The whole set up as a football club and business is crumbling in reduced speed. It hurts to watch this happening in front of our eyes as I have only supported Manchester United football club all my life. Just like how King Eric Cantona would always say "You can change your wife, change your politics, change your religion but you can never, never change your favourite football team". Till my last breath, Glory Glory ManUtd. United for Life!

snippet.textDisplay: The problem since Fergie retired is we have hired a new manager every 24 months. That only works if you have Messi or Ronaldo in your squad surrounded by world class talent. I hope Ole stays at least 2 more years.
